('40000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003','Choosing the Right Computer Course for Your Goals','choosing-the-right-computer-course','Start with your current skill level and the tasks you need to perform at work or while job seeking.','The right computer course depends on your starting point and your goals. Beginners benefit from a computer literacy foundation. Learners who already understand basic computer use may be ready for intermediate training or a focused Microsoft course.

For organisations, a group training discussion can identify skill gaps and create a programme suited to the team''s needs.','/images/blog-course-choice.svg','/images/blog-course-choice.svg','How to Choose a Computer Course | New Era','Choose the right computer training programme based on your goals and current skill level.','published','["Training Advice","Skills Development"]',null,'2026-04-20T08:00:00+02:00')
